Definition.WordDefinition: Jamaican \Ja*mai"can\, a. Of or pertaining to Jamaica. -- n. A native or inhabitant of Jamaica. [1913 Webster]
Jamaican adj : of or relating to Jamaica (the island or the country) or to its inhabitants; "Jamaican rum"; "the Jamaican Prime Minister" n : a native or inhabitant of Jamaica
